INSERT INTO `pcharacter` VALUES (1,1,'Ella',26,'Female','Ella is on the run - after a physical encounter between herself and her abusive husband, which ended with him falling down some stairs and hurting his head pretty badly. He is in a coma but Ella thinks he is dead because she fled the scene, believing that she wouldn\'t get a fair trial. But Ella is about to learn that you can\'t just run away from your problems - they always catch up with you.','Protagonist','2015-12-12 00:25:24','2015-12-12 00:25:24'),(2,1,'Rita',30,'Female','Rita is Ella\'s favourite cousin - these two became each others\' surrogate sisters growing up due to lack of real sisters. They were very close. Rita is a few years older than Ella and Ella looks up to her.','Protagonist','2015-12-12 00:26:33','2015-12-12 00:26:33'),(3,1,'Mike',34,'Male','Rita\'s husband. Mike has made his own family.','Other','2015-12-12 00:27:14','2015-12-24 15:50:10'),(4,1,'Hunter',28,'Male','Hunter is a serious, studious man whose past is haunting him. He seems to be able to read people very well. He is friendly but reserved, kind and fair. He won\'t let people get too close to him, though - it\'s not that he\'s afraid of being hurt, it\'s more than he\'s afraid of hurting them.','Love Interest','2015-12-12 00:29:08','2015-12-12 00:29:08'),(5,1,'Danny',29,'Male','Doesn\'t take himself too seriously, likes to enjoy life, very laid back and easy going. Bit of a womanizer though.','Love Interest','2015-12-12 00:29:52','2015-12-12 00:29:52'),(6,1,'Sara',25,'Female','Hunter\'s sister. Sara takes an instant disliking to Ella - she doesn\'t like people who hide things. She knows her brother is into Ella but doesn\'t approve. She is determined to find out what Ella is hiding and expose her.','Skeptic','2015-12-12 00:30:50','2015-12-12 00:30:50'),(7,1,'Sam',29,'Male','Ella\'s abusive husband. Hid his abusive side well up until he and Ella were married, and then became a control freak who always had to have his own way. Whenever Ella tried to challenge him he would get abusive - first verbally, then psychologically and finally physically. Ella thinks the accident that is the result of an altercation between them has killed him but it only put him in a coma for a couple of days. When he wakes up he tells the police that Ella tried to kill him.','Antagonist','2015-12-16 23:30:43','2015-12-16 23:30:43'),(16,36,'Ella',35,'Female','A modern career woman who has terrible luck with men. She\'s at the point where she wants to settle down but dating just isn\'t working out for her. A chance encounter with a nice man sets off a romance that could be \'the one\' for her. Or could it? Sometimes things aren\'t as they seem...','Protagonist','2016-05-08 13:19:19','2016-05-08 13:19:20'),(17,36,'Drew',42,'Male','Peter seems like the perfect guy to Ella - intelligent, handsome, charming and creative. And best of all, he\'s single and finds her attractive too!','Love Interest','2016-05-14 02:36:26','2016-05-20 20:27:28'),(18,41,'Sammie',18,'Female','A typical straight-A student headed for an Ivy league college hoping to study veterinary sciences. A responsible, compassionate, well-rounded individual. Is secretly hot for Malcolm. Might be willing to throw all morals out the window (and her friendship with Cady) for one night of bliss with Malcom...','Protagonist','2016-05-14 02:39:34','2016-05-14 02:39:34'),(19,41,'Elton',18,'Male','Sammie\'s male best friend, Elton comes from old money. He is prone to exploiting others for his own personal gain and gets angry when things don\'t go his way. Secretly in love with Sammie but also secretly knows she would never see him as anything more than a friend. Father wants him to study business/law but Elton can\'t think of anything he\'d rather do less... Secretly cuts himself and is into BDSM.','Protagonist','2016-05-14 02:39:51','2016-05-14 02:39:52'),(20,41,'Louise',18,'Male','Incredibly hot but not very bright, with a rather strange lack of self-esteem. Allows herself to be treated badly by boyfriend Elton because he\'s rich and marrying him would be an easy option as she really doesn\'t know what she\'s going to do with her life. Might be in the closet...','Protagonist','2016-05-14 02:40:09','2016-05-14 02:40:09'),(21,41,'John',19,'Male','The comic relief - a laid-back stoner who surfs and hosts parties. Doesn\'t do too well in school but doesn\'t particularly care. Would be perfectly content to work in a bowling alley for the rest of his life. Lacks common sense but is a decent enough person. May be a drug dealer...','Protagonist','2016-05-14 02:40:35','2016-05-14 02:40:35'),(22,41,'Katy',17,'Female','Artsy and ultra-feminist with a major chip on her shoulder, Cady is brilliant, though, receiving a fine arts scholarship to a prestigious arts school - hundreds of kilometres away from where her boyfriend, Malcolm, is due to go to college on a football scholarship. Cady is edgy, raw and temperamental. Nobody quite understands why her and boyfriend Malcolm date - perhaps they are reliving their childhood attachment traumas with one another. In any case, the two are volatile with each other and volatile without. Wouldn\'t it be interesting if Cady discovered she was pregnant???','Protagonist','2016-05-14 02:40:52','2016-05-14 02:40:52'),(23,41,'Malcolm',18,'Male','Typical alpha-male jock. Very into demonstrating his physical prowess at any opportunity. Would defend any one of his friends in an instant, even if they didn\'t really need defending. Dates his polar opposite Cady. Plans on attending a nearby college on a football scholarship. May indulge in steroid use...','Protagonist','2016-05-14 02:41:12','2016-05-14 02:41:12'),(24,34,'You',32,'Male','You','Protagonist','2016-05-14 02:48:25','2016-05-14 02:48:25'),(25,34,'Him',56,'Male','Him, El Creepo','Antagonist','2016-05-14 02:48:49','2016-05-14 02:48:49'),(26,42,'Sidney Milton',23,'Male','Your typical struggling artist. Lives in a studio apartment in a trendy locale. Doesn\'t own any furniture. Has only sold three paintings.','Protagonist','2016-05-14 02:56:53','2016-05-14 02:56:54'),(27,42,'Diana Carruthers',57,'Female','A wealthy New York socialite whose art dealing husband has just had an affair with a much younger woman. Diana has come up with a cunning plan for revenge.','Antagonist','2016-05-14 02:57:21','2016-05-14 02:57:21'),(28,42,'Philip Carruthers',65,'Male','A fine art dealer who was born to wealthy parents on the upper east side of New York city. Recently had an affair with a much younger woman. Is always on the lookout for art from dead or dying artists - it\'s basically how he makes his money - he\'s like the ambulance chaser of the art world.','Other','2016-05-14 02:57:48','2016-05-14 02:57:48'),(29,42,'Lindsey Fox',26,'Female','The fine art review writer for Maxist Magazine. She thinks our protagonist is very sweet and very cute but has doubts as to whether he really is in fact dying.','Love Interest','2016-05-14 02:58:31','2016-05-14 02:58:31'),(30,36,'Susan',29,'Female','Assistant Marketing Director at Magnusson Corporation','Antagonist','2016-05-15 14:38:35','2016-06-08 14:29:11'),(31,36,'Craig',37,'Male','Ella\'s adversary, the QA Manager at the company','Antagonist','2016-05-15 14:39:07','2016-05-15 14:39:07'),(32,36,'Bill',47,'Male','Ella\'s boss','Mentor','2016-05-15 14:40:06','2016-05-15 14:40:06'),(33,36,'Sylvia',33,'Female','Ella\'s best friend','Sidekick','2016-05-15 14:40:33','2016-05-15 14:40:33'),(34,36,'Jayne',38,'Female','Drew\'s ex partner - perfection itself - also in the magazine industry. Long, blonde hair and blue eyes. Very good looking, very witty.','Other','2016-05-20 20:28:41','2016-05-20 20:28:41');
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `pcharacter` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

--
-- Table structure for table `plotpoint`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `plotpoint`;
/*!40101 SET @saved_cs_client     = @@character_set_client */;
/*!40101 SET character_set_client = utf8 */;
CREATE TABLE `plotpoint` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `project_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `title` tinytext COLLATE utf8_unicode_ci NOT NULL,
  `number` int(11) NOT NULL,
  `content` text COLLATE utf8_unicode_ci NOT NULL,
  `plotpointtype` enum('Exposition','Conflict','Rising Action','Climax','Falling Action','Resolution','Story') COLLATE utf8_unicode_ci DEFAULT NULL,
  `dateCreated` datetime NOT NULL,
  `dateModified` datetime NOT NULL,
  `chapter_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (`id`),
  KEY `IDX_D24156D166D1F9C` (`project_id`),
  KEY `IDX_D24156D579F4768` (`chapter_id`),
  CONSTRAINT `FK_D24156D166D1F9C` FOREIGN KEY (`project_id`) REFERENCES `project` (`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  CONSTRAINT `FK_D24156D579F4768` FOREIGN KEY (`chapter_id`) REFERENCES `chapter` (`id`) ON DELETE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=44 DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8 COLLATE=utf8_unicode_ci;
/*!40101 SET character_set_client = @saved_cs_client */;

--
-- Dumping data for table `plotpoint`
--

LOCK TABLES `plotpoint` WRITE;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `plotpoint` DISABLE KEYS */;
INSERT INTO `plotpoint` VALUES (1,1,'Ella arrives in Greenville',1,'Ella arrives in Greenville on the run from the police. Hunter and Danny see her in the diner and speculate. She calls Rita, who comes to pick her up, and tells her about what she\'s running from - an abusive husband that has falsely accused her of attempted murder. Rita offers her a place to stay for as long as she needs it.','Exposition','2015-12-11 20:06:00','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(2,1,'Ella meets Hunter',2,'Ella stumbles upon Hunter undressing outside his trailer. There is undeniable chemistry between them. But when Hunter sees that Ella is wearing a wedding ring he forces himself not to feel desire for her. He introduces her to the others and despite deciding not to act on his desire for her he sees how uncomfortable Mike\'s questions are for her and steps in to help her.','Conflict','2015-12-17 20:22:12','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(3,1,'Sara hates Ella',3,'Ella meets the rest of the gang, including Sara, Hunter\'s sister - and Sara takes an instant disliking to her. She suggests Ella take the cleaning job at the Sheriff\'s Office - but of course Ella can\'t take that job. Sara thinks Ella is above the job. The gang are riding to the next town over the next day where Ella can get a copy of the latest paper for the whole region to look for jobs - Danny and Hunter both offer to take Ella but Hunter claims she is safer with him. Ella accepts the offer. Sara isn\'t too happy.','Conflict','2015-12-24 15:51:12','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(4,1,'Ella and Hunter grow closer as they spend time together',4,'Ella\'s desire grows as Hunter takes Ella for a bike ride. She gets the paper. On the way back they get drenched in the rain. When they get back to the house they peel off their clothes revealing soaked, transparent undergarments. The sexual tension between them continues to build. Hunter lets Ella take a shower first. Hunter ends up getting hypothermia. Ella feels responsible and looks after him, warming him up with her body. In his delirious state, he wonders that Ella hasn\'t left him to fend for himself when sick like his alcoholic mother would have. He says something to her about it. She tells him of course she wouldn\'t leave him like that. Things get heated... Hunter is conscious but Ella doesn\'t know he is. She stops it before it goes too far anyway. Sara returns home and, ever overprotective of her big brother, shoos Ella away.','Rising Action','2015-12-24 15:52:21','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(5,1,'Hunter saves Ella',5,'Hunter stays home from work, still feverish and sick. Ella continues to take care of him - no one else is around. There are no suitable jobs in the paper. When Mike comes home he tells Ella there\'s a job open at the mill because one of the receptionists is pregnant (or something). Hunter is a lot better and will return to work the next day. Rita will drive Ella in to apply for the job. They offer Ella a trial. One of her tasks is to go grab some files from the onsite foreman\'s cabin and bring the back to the office. Ella has a stupid accident... Drops them or something, and in trying to chase the papers around, puts herself in harm\'s way. Hunter spots her and saves her. He is really annoyed that she put herself in danger, (he often had to rescue his alcoholic mother). He says it should be up to her husband, not him, to be the one saving her and looking out for her. He doesn\'t make a move to hurt her, though, like her ex husband would have, and seems to soften a bit when Ella apologises. None-the-less, Ella is incredibly upset.','Conflict','2015-12-24 15:52:57','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(6,1,'The Fair',7,'Ella asks Mike and Rita about Hunter - they tell her about his past. She understands now. he returns home and apologises to her. She accepts. He asks her to go to the fair that weekend and support him in the wood chopping contest - he wants to beat Mike for once. She agrees, even though she doesn\'t want to run into the Sheriff. Now that she knows about his past and how he feels about her in light of it she wants to prove to him that she can be depended upon. Just as Hunter wins the competition and looks for her in the crowd, the Sheriff spots Ella, calling for backup on his walkie talkie; Ella makes a run for it. Later Hunter is upset at Ella for abandoning him, but doesn\'t get angry and take it out on her like Sam would have. Instead he walks away.','Rising Action','2016-01-10 03:00:57','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(7,1,'Sara finds out about Ella',9,'Sara comes home later - and tells them all about Ella. Ella is horrified - she tells them her story, though, and they all forgive her, even Sara.','Conflict','2016-01-10 03:03:36','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(8,1,'Hunter wants Ella',10,'When Hunter realises Ella\'s marriage is over - and for good reasons - he tells Ella how he feels. Ella pretends she doesn\'t feel the same way - she wants him to hate her so that her abandoning him doesn\'t hurt him so much. Later on she leaves on a bus really early in the morning (the same one she came in on) so that Hunter and Rita and the rest of the gang can\'t be implicated in helping her evade arrest.','Conflict','2015-12-24 15:54:32','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(9,1,'Hunter tracks Ella down',11,'Hunter tracks Ella down and convinces her to come back. He again confesses his feelings for her. Ella responds in kind. They make love under the stars and return to the house.','Climax','2015-12-24 15:55:18','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(10,1,'Ella turns herself in',12,'Hunter, Rita and everyone else convince Ella to turn herself in and tell her side of the story. They come up with a plan: Ella has to pretend that she\'s willing to consider going back to Sam in order to get him to admit on tape that he was abusive towards her. As Hunter overhears Ella talking to Sam about going back to him he grows worried. After Ella has spoken to Sam and gotten the evidence she needed, she tells Hunter she needs time to herself to think.','Conflict','2015-12-24 15:56:27','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(11,1,'The charges against Ella are dropped in light of new evidence',13,'The charges against Ella are dropped in light of the evidence - Sam admitting to Ella that he was abusive towards her (she recorded him saying it).','Resolution','2015-12-24 16:02:19','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(12,1,'Ella and Hunter get together',14,'... Ella tells Hunter she loves him. They get together. Make love again?','Resolution','2015-12-24 16:02:52','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(14,1,'Hunter\'s Dream Job',6,'Hunter is good with people - knowing what they want or need and knowing how to lead them in order to get them to do what needs to be done. He has taken a series of laboring jobs ever since his mother abandoned the family. He knows how to manage the mill better than the current managers and this is evident when Ella, not really knowing what she is doing, messes up the rosters that have been created (she loses them or shreds them or something) and Hunter steps in to save the day and makes even better schedules. The big boss notices Ella\'s improved schedule and asks her about it; she comes clean and admits it\'s Hunter\'s handiwork. The boss talks to Hunter and tells him that if he studies management then there\'s a guaranteed job there for him. Hunter realises that the nearest college is so far away he wouldn\'t  be able to attend and keep working at the same time so he declines. Ella confronts him about his decision, asking him why - he tells her he can\'t just stop working, he has to keep looking after Sara and contributing to Mike and Rita\'s household funds. Ella tells him that Sara is old enough to look after herself now and Mike and Rita would be okay with him studying and that he should go to school if he really wants to. Hunter gets angry and says he won\'t ignore his responsibilities like she obviously has. This upsets her.','Rising Action','2016-01-22 12:26:36','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(15,1,'Ella\'s Dream Job',8,'Ella\'s husband Sam got her a job when they first married with his friend (the lawyer) doing reception at his law firm. He did this so he could keep an eye on her, know her whereabouts at all times and exert control over her. Her passion, though, was always with baking. Sam would never encourage her though - he was a fitness fanatic and didn\'t want her to get fat so he told her not to bother too much with it. After Ella screws up her job at the mill, she could notice in the gazette that a town fair is coming up and that a stall costs $30. She could formulate a plan to sell some of her baked goods to raise some money for her board. Hunter could give her business tips being the manager that he is and she could get catering orders from it.','Rising Action','2016-01-22 12:34:40','2016-05-16 19:27:19',NULL),(21,36,'Online Dating Sucks',2,'Ella is a 35 year old professional woman looking for love. She finds most of the men who populate online dating websites are only after something casual, and they carry a lot of baggage.','Exposition','2016-05-08 18:10:58','2016-05-08 23:16:37',NULL),(22,36,'Peter is Dead',1,'In the beginning, the Prologue, Peter lies on the ground dead, having fallen from the top of the carpark opposite the Magnusson Corporation building. Ella is bemoaning the death of the \'love of her life\'. She finally found him after many trials and heartaches and now he is dead. So how did he end up dead... And what happens next?','Climax','2016-05-08 18:13:57','2016-05-08 21:36:20',NULL),(23,36,'Meet Cute',8,'Ella meets Peter while waiting for late public transport. They hit it off over coffee and then decide to take the bus to work. Peter promises to send Ella a copy of the magazine he edits.','Rising Action','2016-05-08 20:47:50','2016-05-08 23:28:52',NULL),(24,36,'A New Project',3,'The Magnusson Corporation is so pleased with the job Ella\'s team did on their last project that they want to hire them again - and give them a high level of access in the process. Bill, Ella\'s boss, has himself and Ella in mind for promotions if all goes well. Ella has mixed feelings about that but keeps them to herself.','Rising Action','2016-05-08 20:52:29','2016-05-08 23:28:52',NULL),(25,36,'Singles Parties',4,'She tries singles parties with her friends but finds that there is a lot of competition and ugly, undesirable men are suddenly in the power position. She knows it\'s not a good idea to chase men as they don\'t value women who chase them anyway. So the situation is just bad all around.','Exposition','2016-05-08 23:21:23','2016-05-08 23:28:52',NULL),(26,36,'Social Groups with Single People',5,'She joins some social groups that include single people but begins to find herself invisible at these events - if a younger woman sits down the man she was talking to suddenly forgets she exists. The pain of being invisible is a bit much to bear.','Exposition','2016-05-08 23:22:34','2016-05-08 23:28:52',NULL),(27,36,'Gym',6,'She finds it annoying that she must continue to go to the gym and keep in shape given the current state of affairs, and even the gym itself becomes something of a hostile environment.','Exposition','2016-05-08 23:23:27','2016-05-08 23:28:52',NULL),(28,36,'Self Help Groups',7,'Something about self help groups...','Exposition','2016-05-08 23:27:12','2016-05-08 23:27:12',NULL),(29,41,'The Kids Prepare for their Upcoming Trip',1,'We get to know the characters and their personalities, and, most importantly, how they interact with one another as they prepare for their upcoming camping trip.','Exposition','2016-05-14 02:42:53','2016-05-14 02:42:53',NULL),(30,41,'They arrive at the cabin in the forest',2,'They basically continue to settle in and we continue to get to know them. Perhaps a few oddities might become apparent as they habituate themselves to their new environment.','Exposition','2016-05-14 02:43:21','2016-05-14 02:43:21',NULL),(31,41,'Tensions grow',3,'Things between Malcolm and Katy aren\'t great. They have a huge argument and Katy goes off into the woods. Elton, John and Louise are indulging in drugs out at the lake and Malcolm and Sammie are left alone together in the cabin. They talk and bond a bit - there could even be the briefest tease of a possible kiss. Elton comes back to get some snacks, sensing the attraction between them (maybe even stumbling upon them almost kissing). He delivers some rather cutting remarks to Sammie and leaves again just as Katy comes back. Malcolm then leaves and Sammie is slotted into the role of consoling Katy, having to pretend the whole time that she isn\'t secretly wishing the demise of the relationship between her best friend and Malcolm so she can have him for herself.','Exposition','2016-05-14 02:43:59','2016-05-14 02:43:59',NULL),(32,41,'Yet More Tensions',4,'As John, Elton and Louise are smoking marijuana together, John notices the dismissive and at times abusive way Elton treats Louise. He makes a few comments about it but John pretty much alludes to the fact that Louise is just a gold digger who deserves what she gets anyway. When Elton goes to get snacks John tries to convince Louise that she doesn\'t deserve Elton\'s treatment of her; she can\'t see his point of view, though, as she truly believes she deserves it. When Elton comes back he displays an almost token gesture of kindness towards Louise in an obvious attempt to appease John. John seems satisfied... For the time being.','Exposition','2016-05-14 02:44:29','2016-05-14 02:44:30',NULL),(33,34,'Moving In',1,'You have just moved to a new house. You unpack your belongings and go to bed.','Exposition','2016-05-14 02:52:53','2016-05-14 02:52:54',NULL),(34,34,'Awoken',2,'You are woken suddenly by pain and notice that the manhole above your bed is open. You can hear noises downstairs. You freak out a bit as you consider your next move.','Conflict','2016-05-14 02:53:23','2016-05-14 02:53:23',NULL),(35,34,'Downstairs',3,'You decide to go downstairs, quietly, in the dark. There is someone down there, though, and you decide to escape through the front door.','Rising Action','2016-05-14 02:53:58','2016-05-14 02:53:58',NULL),(36,42,'Diana Carruthers sees Sidney Milton and his paintings',2,'Diana Carruthers has just learned that her art dealing husband has been cheating on her with his much younger secretary. She is in so much shock that she gives the taxi driver the wrong address and he drops her off at a strip of cafes near a subway entrance. As she stops to look at the paintings of a struggling yet extremely handsome young man she comes up with a diabolical plan for revenge. She asks the man his name and leaves; he is disappointed - he was sure it was going to be a sale.','Exposition','2016-05-14 03:01:05','2016-05-16 19:29:27',NULL),(37,42,'Diana Carruthers contacts Sidney Milton to arrange a meeting',3,'Diana contacts Sidney to arrange a meeting to talk about his paintings - he is thrilled that someone has taken an interest in him; when he googles her he discovers she is the wife of a well known art dealer. It\'s as if all his dreams have come true. She tells him that while she appreciates his vision and technique as an artist, her husband really actually only deals in art from artists that are already dead or dying. She tells him that if he were to pretend he had cancer or some other fatal disease she wouldn\'t let her husband in on the truth. Then she tells him about the failure rate of struggling artists in New York. She tells him the choice is his and leaves him to decide.','Exposition','2016-05-14 03:01:37','2016-05-16 19:29:27',NULL),(38,42,'Welcome to the Dark Side',4,'Sidney decides that as a struggling artist he should just do the Faustian-type deal with Mrs. Carruthers as he may not get another chance. He doesn\'t question her motives in the whole thing - he simply believes she sees promise in his work and wants to help him for altruistic motives. He calls her back up and agrees to the meeting. She tells him she has a dear doctor friend who can help them in corroborating Sidney\'s story and that all they have to do is meet with her husband. She will present Sidney to him along with his art at a special dinner held in his honour. She is certain that her husband will likely agree to represent Sidney once he hears about the boy\'s fatal illness. Sidney is happy but a little disappointed that he has to stoop to such levels to gain recognition, but at least it will enable him to rid himself of his legal troubles.','Conflict','2016-05-14 03:04:54','2016-05-16 19:29:27',NULL),(39,42,'Sidney hits Rock Bottom',1,'So at this point Sidney is struggling so much that he\'s about to lose his studio apartment - his job on the side as a waiter is gone because he spilled some soup on someone important and they are now suing him for damages. He can\'t get access to legal aid and when he approached a lawyer they told him it was going to cost a minimum of twenty grand just to represent him. He is considering either representing himself or taking out a loan. When he tries to read some legal documents he realises he doesn\'t have a head for it. His parents are really disappointed in him and can\'t help him out either. He is in dire straits.','Exposition','2016-05-14 03:05:30','2016-05-16 19:29:27',NULL),(40,42,'The Secret of My Success...',5,'Carruthers agrees to deal Sidney\'s art.  Lyndsey Fox reviews the art very favourably, and it becomes the toast of the town - people are buying it and paying even more than Sidney could ever have hoped for. The Carruthers are making a fortune. Sidney has paid his lawyers and they are settling the lawsuit. All is going well.','Rising Action','2016-05-14 03:07:13','2016-05-16 19:29:27',NULL),(41,42,'Complications Arise',6,'Sidney is falling in love with Lyndsey Fox but she has begun to ask questions. The public is asking about Sidney\'s illness - how fatal is it, really, if he\'s still around and seemingly as healthy as ever? Reporters are asking questions. His parents have heard about his illness and are devastated. Sidney feels very bad.','Rising Action','2016-05-14 03:08:26','2016-05-16 19:29:27',NULL),(42,42,'Real Rock Bottom',7,'Our hero really hits rock bottom as Diana Carruthers reveals to everyone in a press release that Sidney is not in dying, nor even ill at all, and that her husband knew all along... Lyndsey is disgusted with Sidney for going along with such a plan and swears off him, Mr. Carruthers is livid with him, and the people who bought his art want to return it but Mr. Carruthers won\'t give them a refund. They decide to sue, and Sidney goes to Mrs. Carruthers to confront her about the situation and ask why she did what she did; she tells him not to worry, that the contracts she had drawn up and had her husband signed protect Sidney from any potential lawsuits. She tells him about the affair Philip had and how devastated she was - Sidney still can\'t believe she could do what she did to him, an innocent bystander in the whole thing. She shrugs. \"All is fair in love and war.\"','Rising Action','2016-05-14 03:10:56','2016-05-16 19:29:27',NULL),(43,42,'Humiliated and Lost',8,'Sidney is humiliated; the whole of New York and the art world at large knows him as a fraud. He can never sell another painting. His dreams are dead. He has lost Lyndsey who he believes was the perfect woman for him and his parents are even more disappointed in him than they were before. He starts doing drugs to cope with the emotional pain, and becomes obsessed with Diana Carruthers who has moved out of her mansion and into an apartment. He begins to stalk her and finds out some of her secrets... Secrets she may not want to come out in the midst of such a messy and potentially lucrative divorce settlement.','Rising Action','2016-05-14 03:13:21','2016-05-16 19:29:27',NULL);
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `plotpoint` ENABLE KEYS */;
UNLOCK TABLES;

--
-- Table structure for table `project`
--

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS `project`;
/*!40101 SET @saved_cs_client     = @@character_set_client */;
/*!40101 SET character_set_client = utf8 */;
CREATE TABLE `project` (
  `id` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
  `user_id` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,
  `title` tinytext COLLATE utf8_unicode_ci NOT NULL,
  `projectType` enum('Novel','Novella','Non Fiction Book','Biography','Autobiography','Article','Poem','Short Story','Essay','Childrens Book','Play','ScreenPlay','Journal') COLLATE utf8_unicode_ci DEFAULT NULL,
