a. I just wanted to see her again.\r\nMike didn\'t look convinced. If you were planning on visiting, you could have set it up in advance. He regarded her with suspicion. \r\nShe shrugged. I\'m very impulsive, I guess.\r\nFunny, he said, Rita always told me that she was the impulsive one and you were the level headed shy one. He continued to stare at her. So how long do you think you\'ll be staying for?\r\nUh... I\'m not sure...\r\n\r\nHunter could see that Ella was really struggling. He was convinced by now from all that he had seen and heard from her that she was in some kind of trouble. As Mike questioned her, Hunter could see her breathing becoming more rapid and her chest rise and fall with more definition  not that he had been staring at her chest.. Her eyes were very wide and she laughed nervously. \r\n\r\nHunter suddenly felt the need to protect her from Mike. He couldn\'t stand to see her in any kind of distress. So he interrupted. \r\nI think Ella\'s still probably very tired, Mike. She covered a lot of distance to get here. I just wanted to introduce you to her but I think she needs some rest now. Ella nodded and looked at Hunter gratefully. Mike threw the oily rag down on the floor. Sure, he replied, and gave Hunter a steely glare. Then he went back behind his bike to continue working on it. See you at dinner, Ella.\r\n\r\n As Hunter led Ella back to the house, Danny stayed behind with Mike. See you later, Ella.\r\nLater Danny, she replied. Later Mike. Mike merely grunted. \r\n\r\nInside the house, Ella said, Thank you for doing that.\r\nDoing what? Hunter stopped and turned to look at Ella questioningly. He wondered if she would open up to him now. Ella averted her eyes from his. You were right - I am quite tired.\r\nHe touched her arm gently. It felt like a mild jolt of electricity that travelled along her arm and through the rest of her body. Go lie down, then. Rita will come get you for supper. \r\n\r\nShe nodded. She almost didn\'t want to move away from him. For some reason she felt incredibly safe around him. But she knew she had to, and so she turned and went to her room. She lay on the bed, touching her arm in the same spot he had just touched her. She smiled, imagining him touching her elsewhere.',4519,'chapter'),(3,1,'3','Desire continues to grow between Hunter and Ella - but will Hunter let himself go after a married woman?','Desire Grows','2015-12-25 13:38:24','2016-02-07 02:49:17','A few hours later, Rita knocked on her door softly. \r\nCome in, Ella called out. Rita entered the room and sat on the edge of Ella\'s bed. How are you?\r\nI managed to catch a few hours sleep at least. Still thinking about Sam though.\r\n\r\nIt was the truth  just about every time she had been close to drifting off to sleep, her thoughts had been drawn to her husband   but not for the reasons Rita probably thought they would be. \r\nYou shouldn\'t be alone right now. It\'s no good for you, especially not at a time like this. Come out and have dinner with us.\r\n\r\nElla remembered how Mike had acted towards her in the garage earlier. She wasn\'t exactly in a hurry to talk to him again. Mike was asking me all these questions earlier, she explained. I kind of came in here to escape him.\r\nRita frowned. He\'s just curious. Don\'t be intimidated by him. If he starts up again, I\'ll talk to him. She patted Ella\'s arm reassuringly. Don\'t worry.\r\nThanks, Rita. You\'ve been so kind to me. I don\'t know what I\'d do -\r\nRita rolled her eyes and then smiled warmly at Ella. It\'s no problem. I really missed you, you know.\r\nMe too.\r\n\r\nThe rest of the gang were seated at the dining table already when Ella followed Rita out to the kitchen  Mike, Danny and Hunter, and also a young woman with hair the same colour as Hunter\'s. Her eyes were slightly bluer than his but there was really no mistaking the resemblance between them  this must be Hunter\'s sister. She smiled at the girl. \"Hello. I\'m Ella. Nice to meet you.\"\r\nSara