it. \r\n\r\nWhen another silence descended over the table like a dense fog Sara suddenly asked, How long will you be staying with us, Ella? There was hostility in her almost accusatory tone. \r\nRita quickly interjected, She doesn\'t know yet, Sara. I told you that before.\r\nSara raised an eyebrow. Well if it\'s going to be a while, are you going to contribute to the household budget?\r\nElla stole a glance at Rita, then at Mike. Rita shrugged apologetically but Mike looked as though he was interested in hearing her answer the question. \r\nIt\'s a bit early to be talking about that, isn\'t it Sara? Hunter said in Ella\'s defence. Ella felt the stirrings of desire burn even hotter in the area below her stomach as once again Hunter came to her rescue. \r\nI only mentioned it because there\'s a job going in Beatties Cove, Sara replied. It\'s at the Sheriff\'s Office, cleaning. You could probably have the job if you wanted it.\r\n\r\nElla almost choked on her food at Sara\'s suggestion. She was on the run from the police The last thing she would ever want to do would be to parade herself around in front of a Sheriff all day every day! She looked down at her plate, trying to think of what she could say. The awkward silence was almost deafening as everyone at the table stared at Ella, waiting for her to respond. \r\n\r\nShe seemed unable to come up with a suitable reason as to why the job wouldn\'t suit her. After waiting a few moments, Sara said, Oh, are you too good for a cleaning job? What did you do before, anyway? Something fancy? Doctor? Lawyer?\r\nNo, not at all, Ella replied. Her face was turning red and her voice was wavering. I was in office administration, actually... The cleaning job wouldn\'t suit me because... I have severe allergies... And asthma. \r\n\r\nIt was the best Ella could come up with. Mike laughed uproariously. Rita shot him a warning look but it didnt stop him. Sara smirked. Even Hunter was trying not to smile. \r\n\r\nElla was embarrassed, but glad when it seemed like they were clearly going to drop the issue. She sank back into her chair and breathed a sigh of relief. But then Mike said, If you are going to be here for a while, it might be an idea to see if any jobs around here do actually suit you. You should take a look at the Beattie\'s Cove Gazette. \r\nBut only if you feel like it, Rita added. \r\nElla smiled at them. It sounds like a good idea. Ill do that.\r\nWe\'re going for a ride tomorrow on the bikes, Hunter said then. Over to Beatties Cove. I can bring you back a paper if you want.\r\nOh really? Is everyone going?\r\nYeah, everyone except for Sara, because she\'s working. \r\nSara scowled. Ella ignored her, replying, I\'ve never ridden on a motorbike before. Is it as fun as it looks?\r\nYou should come! You can ride with me, Danny said. \r\nElla shook her head. \"I don\'t know...\"\r\n\"Oh come on,\" Danny insisted. \"We can\'t all just go out for a ride on a nice day and leave you here by yourself. It\'d be too mean.\"\r\n\r\nHunter sighed loudly. He had actually been meaning to do just that - to leave here in the house by herself - she seemed like she needed time to think and sort through some stuff anyway. But if Danny was going to offer to give her a ride, then he was going to have to step in. Danny was notoriously reckless, and Hunter couldn\'t have it on his head if she got hurt and he could have prevented it. \r\n\r\nNo way. If she\'s never ridden before she should ride with me. Then she has less chance of dying.\r\nElla\'s eyes widened. Excuse me?\r\nDanny laughed. He\'s joking, just joking. But seriously. Ride with me and it\'ll be a ride you\'ll never forget.\r\nMike groaned. Rita rolled her eyes and laughed. \r\nHunter said, Ride with me. I\'m more responsible than he is and I\'ll make sure you\'re safe.\r\n\r\nElla considered for a moment. She didn\'t like the idea of coming off a motorbike and breaking her neck. But then again, Hunter didn\'t seem all that keen on being around her. She remembered the way he had turned cold when he had seen her wedding ring. She tested him to see if he was serious about the offer. \r\n\r\nIs it really safe?\r\nIt\'ll be safe with me,\" he said begrudgingly. \"Unlike Danny, I won\'t go too fast. And you can make me slow down at any time by squeezing my arm, or my sides.\r\n\r\nElla almost blushed. Squeezing him? She imagined it: her arms would be wrapped around his torso, the insides of her legs would be touching the outsides of his... Their bodies would be close, close enough for her to feel his body heat even, to feel him moving against her...\r\n\r\nHunter said, That\'s a yes, isn\'t it? \r\nElla blushed. Actually I\'m a little scared.\r\nSara suddenly barked out, Hunt, I\'ll ride with you, she can ride with Danny. She gave Ella an icy glare.\r\nYou\'re working tomorrow, Hunter said.\r\nSara replied, I can take a different shift. I want to ride with you. Please?\r\nToo bad, he said. I\'m not letting her go with Danny. He\'s too unpredictable. \r\nDanny grinned devilishly. And that\'s exactly why you should ride with me.\r\nElla shook her head. No, I think if I were to ride with anyone it\'d be Hunter. \r\n\r\nShe tried not to notice how uncomfortable Hunter had seemed just then. She had only meant it would be better to ride with him because it would be safer, not that she longed to feel his body up against hers.\r\n \r\nA wise choice, Rita said. \r\nIt\'s settled then.\r\nHooray, Mike said. Thank Christ for that. Now let\'s clear the table.\r\n\r\nThe next day Ella awoke with an even bigger knot than usual in her stomach  apart from her standard fear of late of the police tracking her down to this sleepy mountain town and arresting her for murder, she now had the accompanying fear that the impending motorcycle ride she had hastily agreed to last night would result in doom and gloom. \r\n\r\nLately, though, she had noticed that in general she had been taking more risks, standing up for herself more and slowly changing from the perennial pushover that everyone took for granted into someone more sure of herself, someone who was more willing to stand up and assert her rights. \r\n\r\nShe supposed that this had been owing to a general sort of dissatisfaction she had been beginning to feel with her life, due mostly to the draining relationship she had endured with her husband for so long, among other things. Such dis-satisfactions tended to build up and up and up until at last they were released in one big, catastrophic rush, as had happened just before she had left Safety Valley. In any case, Ella found herself excited as well as terrified about the bike ride when she stood beside the road at the end of the driveway next to Hunter and his motorcycle. \r\n\r\nRita, Mike and Danny had already left. Hunter had told them that he wanted to take things slowly with Ella and that they should all just go ahead at their normal pace. \r\n\r\nHunter handed Ella some gloves and a helmet. Put these on.\r\n\r\nThe helmet she had a little trouble with; it had a strap that somehow was meant to be secured beneath her chin, but because she had never dealt with one before and also because she couldn\'t see it she couldn\'t manage to get it done up properly. Hunter, having yet to put his own helmet and gloves on, tried to hide his amused smile as he watched her struggle with the strap and loops. Eventually he came to her rescue, his strong, deft fingers pulling and twisting the strap through the loops, touching the underside of her chin now and then, his fingers warm and gentle. The visor of her helmet was still up as he gently wrestled with the straps and as his eyes were intently watching his fingers, she took the opportunity to really drink in the features of his face up close. First she stared at his furrowed blonde brow, at the way the lines between his eyebrows crinkled into a cute little eleven as he concentrated on fastening the strap. Then she looked at the sparkling azure pools that were his eyes - eyes she could almost drown in they were so expressive and beautiful. Her gaze travelled down his long, straight nose then continued down to his soft, velvety lips. She noticed the fine blonde stubble that was starting to make an appearance around his mouth and his finely squared jaw. She imagined how rough it would feel against her cheeks. Then she began to wonder how those soft lips would feel against her own. When his fingers brushed against the underneath of her chin she imagined him gently tilting it up before pressing his lips against hers. She would breathe him in, that musky odour of his, and kiss him back, softly at first and then harder as her desire for him grew and overwhelmed her... \r\n\r\nHe stepped back to admire his handiwork. There you go. All safe and secure.\r\nShe smiled. Thank you. He flipped the visor of her helmet down before putting his own on, then his gloves. He mounted his bike and kicked it to life; it roared once very loudly, and then a few times more as Hunter hit the throttle, before settling down into a slightly softer purr as it idled. Hunter swung his head around to look at Ella. He gestured for her to get on. She took a deep breath and approached the bike. \r\n \r\nShe swung one leg over the bike, then shifted so she was sitting on the back of it. Hunter patted his thighs with his hands. He wanted her to scooch into him. She complied rather shyly; soon her thighs were pressed up against his and she leaned up against him so that her breasts were pressed tightly against his back. She circled his midsection with her arms and put her head on his left shoulder so she could see where they were going. Beforehand they had agreed on a system; if he was going too fast she was to squeeze his sides really tightly with her hands.\r\n\r\nAs the bike rumbled underneath her, she felt its deep vibrations course through her body; they had an almost numbing, calming effect on her. The bike was so intensely loud that it blotted out