tly again, her thighs tightening around his, her breasts pressing even more tightly up against his back. But he was so cautious, so careful and in control that she would quickly loosen up and trust in him completely again. In this way she found that she was able to let herself go and enjoy the experience fully. \r\n\r\nAs she found herself completely in the moment, she found that the past and the future no longer existed. All that she felt was the gentle rising and falling of the bike as it crested small hills, and their weight shifting in unison with the bike as they rounded the curves of the road. All she could smell were the rotting leaves and dense, damp forest all around them. All she could hear was the deep rumbling of the motorbike as it echoed against the jutting rocks of the mountain walls. All she could see ahead was the road as it rushed to meet them, the white lines blurring and the sun spotting it now and then as it was able to peak through the high branches of the trees surrounding them.\r\n\r\nEventually they came to Beatties Cove. It was considerably larger than Natchika and housed such conveniences as a primary school, a regular sized supermarket, a few restaurants by the waterfront, some clothing stores Just about everything youd expect from a town of this size. It had an air of commerce about it, and while Ella wouldnt exactly call it a bustling metropolis, it definitely felt much more inhabited than Natchika had.\r\n\r\nHunter pulled over and parked the bike outside the newsagent. Ella disentangled her legs from the bike and gingerly removed her helmet. Hunter switched the bike off and pulled his helmet off as well. Ella was grinning from ear to ear. \r\n\r\n\"Wow,\" she said. \"I feel so relaxed.\"\r\n\"Cheaper than a masseuse,\" Hunter replied. \r\n\r\nHe was surprised to find himself so happy to see her happy. He had almost forgotten the fact that she was married. Instead, thoughts of how it had felt to have her pressed up against him flooded 